<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5363003>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Habitus of Lisubatrus dongzhiweii gen. & sp. nov., male in dorsal (A) and dorsolateral (B) views. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5363003/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5363005>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Morphological details of Lisubatrus dongzhiweii gen. & sp. nov., male. A – left antenna. B–C – head and pronotum, in dorsal (B), and lateral (C) views. D – right elytron. E – meso- and metaventrite. F – abdomen in dorsal view, showing tergites IV–VII. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, F; 0.2 mm in B–E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5363005/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5363007>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Morphological details of Lisubatrus dongzhiweii gen. & sp. nov., male. A – tergite VIII. B – sternite VIII. C–E – aedeagus, in dorsal (C), lateral (D), and ventral (E) views. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5363007/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5363009>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Representatives of the Dendrolasiophilus group of genera.A – Dendrolasiophilus wenhsini Yin & Li, 2013, female. B – Songius hlavaci Zhao, Yin & Li, 2010, male. C – Tangius indicus Yin & Li, 2013, male. D – Maajappia omotonis Nomura, 2010, male. E – Myrmicophila tangliangi Yin & Li, 2011, male (Figs 4A–C reproduced from YIN & LI 2013a,b, 2015, respectively). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5363009/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

